  "Magnetic polarity of the ocean floor switches because of electric currents generated by deep ocean water flow": "",
  "The matching magnetic patterns were caused by lightning strikes that magnetized exposed seafloor rocks equally": "",
  "Magnetic striping provides key evidence for seafloor spreading: as lava solidifies at the ridge, minerals record Earth's magnetic field, and the symmetrical pattern on both sides proves new crust forms equally.": "",
